                <head>Servia.</head>
                <p>George L. Lorillard, Sec. Emb. or Leg. was assigned to serve in Servia as Special
                    Agent to assist the Minister at Bucharest in taking care of American interests
                    and, at the same time acting in representation of Austro-Hungarian interests
                    there. As Special Agent, to enjoy individual rank as Charg√© d'Affaires.</p>
                <p>Lorillard closed the legation at Serbia January 4, 1917, and deposited the
                    archives in the American Embassy at Rome. Lorillard's resignation was accepted
                    Jan. 8, 1917, effective at once.</p>
